# List UI Standard

When creating or editing user-facing list/table screens, use the attendance statistics list as the default pattern.

- Show exactly 10 rows per page for pageable lists.
- Keep the list area height stable. If the last page has fewer than 10 rows, render empty placeholder rows so the pagination stays directly below the 10-row area.
- Put pagination immediately under the list card/table, not fixed to the browser viewport bottom.
- Use one consistent pagination shape: `이전` / `currentPage / totalPages` / `다음`.
- Add a numbering column at the front of each list. Numbers should continue across pages, e.g. page 2 starts at 11.
- Use fixed table/grid columns (`table-fixed`, `colgroup`, or fixed CSS grid tracks) so text does not shift left/right between pages.
- For member/person lists, prefer dropdown filters for `부서` and `목장` instead of long horizontal department tabs.
- Sort 목장 dropdowns numerically when names contain numbers: `제1목장`, `제2목장`, ... `제10목장`, `제11목장`.
- Keep row heights, typography, borders, and colors visually consistent with `AttendanceStatistics`.
